## Conventions

### Naming Conventions
- Files: lowercase with hyphens where needed (`stylesheet.css`, `scripts.js`, `headshot.png`)
- CSS classes: lowercase, hyphen-separated BEM-lite (e.g., `project-card`, `skill-tag`, `contact-link`, `nav-inner`)
- Section IDs in HTML match the nav anchor text in lowercase: `#about`, `#skills`, `#projects`, `#experience`, `#contact`

### Code Style Rules
- No inline `style=""` attributes anywhere in HTML — all styles go in `css/stylesheet.css`
- No `<style>` tags in any HTML file
- Semantic HTML5 elements throughout: `<header>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<footer>`, `<nav>`
- All `<img>` elements must have a descriptive `alt` attribute
- Heading hierarchy must be logical and unbroken: `<h1>` → `<h2>` → `<h3>`
- External links: always `target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"`

### CSS Patterns
- CSS custom properties defined in `:root` for the color palette (`--bg`, `--text`, `--accent`, `--secondary-bg`, `--max-width`)
- Mobile-first base styles with `@media (min-width: ...)` for wider breakpoints
- Max content width constrained with `.container` class set to `max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto`
- Google Fonts loaded via `<link>` in `<head>` — not via `@import` in CSS

